# Python / FastAPI patterns (auto-attached)

This is the "Auto Attached" rule type ‚Äî it enters context when a matching Python file (per the
comma-separated `globs`) is referenced or edited.

- Keep modules single-responsibility: models in `models/schemas.py`, the one model call in
  `services/summarizer.py`, HTTP concerns in `api/`. Dependencies point inward.
- Inject the OpenAI client through a FastAPI dependency; never construct it inside a route so tests
  can pass a mock without monkey-patching.
- Map domain exceptions to status codes in `api/errors.py` (`PayloadTooLargeError`‚Üí413,
  validation‚Üí422, `SummarizerError`‚Üí502). Return `ErrorResponse(error, request_id)` ‚Äî no stack traces.
- Validate with Pydantic v2 `Field` constraints; enforce the 10k-char cap as a route-level 413, not a
  `max_length` (which would wrongly surface as a 422).
- Every test mocks the model client. See @src/summarizer_service/services/summarizer.py for the
  canonical one-call wrapper.
